speech.p: On behalf of all my constituents, I warmly congratulate the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge on the birth of their new

son, Prince George, and wish him a long and happy life. The royal family provide our nation with civility and an example of service and commitment to us all. I know that the new prince and his parents will be given a very warm welcome, should they have occasion to visit Bury, Ramsbotham or Toddington.
